title: Leaves from the journal of our life in the Highlands, from 1848 to 1861.
author: Victoria
snippet: We passed Pitlochrie, a small village, Faskally, a very pretty place of Mr. Butter's, to the left, and then came to the Pass of Killiecrankie, which is quite magnificent ; the road winds along it, and you look down a great height, all wooded on both sides ; the Garry rolling below it.

title: Scotland Picturesque and Traditional. A pilgrimage with staff and knapsack
author: Todd, George Eyre.
snippet: An hour ago these Avaters were pouring through the narroAv Passof Killiecrankie, by the foot of Ben Vrackie, and under the Bridge ofGarry and the dark Avoods of Faskally; and their coldness and theirlimpid clearness as they rush here into the profounder Tay speak yetof their mountain birth.

title: Journal of a Summer Tour in the Perthshire and Inverness-shire Highlands
author: Roger, James Cruikshank.
snippet: Theplace-name Butterstone, it may be mentioned,has its origin in the Norse personal name Butar,which still lingers in the district as a surname,in the family name of the Butters of Faskally.
